\int_{0}^{\infty} \frac{\cos x - e^{-x}}{x} \ dx
J(a)=\frac12\log(a^2+1)-\log(a+1)+C
C
J(a)\to 0
a\to\infty
C=0
J(0)=0
J(a)=\int_0^\infty\frac{\cos x-e^{-x}}{x}e^{-ax}dx
dJ/da=\int_0^\infty(\cos x e^{-ax} -e^{-(1+a)x})dx=a/(a^2+1)-1/(a+1)
\int_0^\infty  {{{\cos x - {e^{ - x}}} \over x}dx}  = \int_0^\infty  {\left( {{s \over {1 + {s^2}}} - {1 \over {1 + s}}} \right)ds}  = \mathop {\lim }\limits_{s \to \infty } \log {{\sqrt {{s^2} + 1} } \over {s + 1}} = 0
